### The DO-178C Framework

**DO-178C** (RTCA/EUROCAE) is the primary document referenced by certification authorities including the FAA, EASA, and Transport Canada to approve software used in commercial civil airborne systems[reference:2]. It defines objectives for planning, development, verification, configuration management, and quality assurance so that airborne software is shown to meet its intended safety objectives[reference:3][reference:4].

**DAL (Design Assurance Level)** — from A (catastrophic) to E (no effect)[reference:5]:

| **DAL Level** | **Description** | **Objectives** |
|---|---|---|
| **DAL A** | Catastrophic failure | 71 objectives — maximum rigor |
| **DAL B** | Hazardous failure | 69 objectives |
| **DAL C** | Major failure | 62 objectives |
| **DAL D** | Minor failure | 26 objectives |
| **DAL E** | No effect | 0 objectives |

**ST-T1024 is designed to meet DAL A/B/C requirements by construction.**

